Singapore Stocks: Golden Agri, Noble Group, Stamford Tyres

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 
2011-03-10T04:53:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/city-developments-singapore-airlines-singapore-stocks-preview.html
Singapore’s  Straits Times Index (FSSTI) 
dropped 0.5 percent to 3,076.43 as of the 12:30 p.m. trading
break. Almost three stocks declined for each that rose in the
benchmark index of 30 companies.  Shares on the measure trade at an average 14.1 times
estimated earnings, compared with about 15.6 times at the end of
2010, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The following shares were among the most active in the
market. Stock symbols are in parentheses after the company name.  Commodity suppliers: The Thomson Reuters/Jefferies CRB
Index, which tracks prices of 19 commodities from copper to corn,
fell 0.2 percent in  New York  yesterday, extending its decline
for a second day.    Noble Group Ltd. (NOBL)  , a Hong Kong-based commodities
supplier, dropped 2.4 percent to S$2.08.  Olam International Ltd. (OLAM) 
, a Singapore-based supplier of agricultural
commodities, slipped 1.9 percent to S$2.66.  Palm-oil producers: Crude palm-oil futures for May delivery
fell as much as 2.9 percent in  Kuala Lumpur  today.    Golden Agri-Resources Ltd. (GGR)  , the world’s second-
biggest palm-oil producer, slipped 1.5 percent to 67.5 Singapore
cents.  First Resources Ltd. (FR)  , an Indonesian palm-oil
producer, fell 0.8 percent to S$1.30.  Indofood Agri Resources
Ltd. (IFAR)  , the palm-oil unit of  Indonesia ’s biggest noodle
maker, declined 1.7 percent to S$2.30.  Stamford Tyres Corp. (STC SP), a Singapore-based retailer
and distributor of tires, rose 1.7 percent to 29.5 Singapore
cents. The company said third-quarter net income increased 26
percent to S$2.9 million from a year earlier.  TTJ Holdings Ltd. (TTJ SP), a supplier of structural steel,
gained 2.6 percent to 19.5  Singapore  cents. The company said
first-half net income doubled to S$4.7 million from S$2.3
million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Burgos in Singapore at 
 jburgos4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at   ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 